main event: A civilian observed a green object with a white rim in the sky in Security, Colorado on March 22, 1966.
interesting points: The object was as bright as a car headlight and appeared at tree top level, angled towards the ground, and disappeared behind trees in 4-5 seconds.
The object had a trail about the length of the object.
The observer had not seen a similar object before.
The observer reported the sighting to the local police on March 23, 1966.
The Air Force requested the observer complete an additional questionnaire for further evaluation of the sighting.
sighted object: a green object with a white rim
